Operators in this industry act as lessors of buildings used as residences or dwellings. Industry participants are owners-lessors of residential buildings and establishments that rent real estate and then act as lessors by subleasing it to others. In addition to apartments, the industry also rents single-family homes and town houses.

# Industry Information
The following industry information has been derived from IBISWorld.com for NAICS – 531110; Apartment Rentals in the US:
Operators in this industry act as lessors of buildings used as residences or dwellings. Industry participants are owners-lessors of residential buildings and establishments that rent real estate and then act as lessors by subleasing it to others. In addition to apartments, the industry also rents single-family homes and town houses.
In addition to apartments, the industry also rents single-family homes and town houses.
